    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1970-09-23T11:40:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1970-09-23T11:40:00-05:00" n="320"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d320">
                <head>320. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in France</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d320fn1">Source: National Archives, <gloss
                            target="#t_RG1">RG</gloss> 59, Central Files 1970–73, AV 12.
                        Confidential; Priority. It was repeated to Amman (Priority), Beirut, Bern,
                        Bonn, Geneva, London, and Tel Aviv.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Paris</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1970-09-23T16:40:00+00:00">September 23, 1970,
                        1640Z</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>12857. Subject: Highjack Hostages Reported Safe. According Quai, French Embassy
                    Amman was informed September 22 by “good source” that highjack hostages all
                    safe. Source told French that hostages were removed from Amman area prior to
                    outbreak of fighting, and are being held elsewhere in Jordan in small groups of
                    about six persons each. Hostages reportedly still under tight <gloss
                        target="#t_PFLP1">PFLP</gloss> guard.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>Culley</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
